Moshood Adebayo Senate President and Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) presidential aspirant,  Dr. Bukola Saraki, has canvassed for emergence of a visionary and ‘digital’ president in the next year’s general elections. Saraki, who spoke while addressing PDP members and delegates at its Lagos State secretariat, at Ikeja, also lamented that Nigeria is currently at a crossroads and needed someone like his person to bail her out. Details later…